                    <th>Feature behavior</th>
                    <th>Best use case</th>
                  </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                  <tr>
                    <td>Ridge</td>
                    <td>Shrinks all coefficients using a penalty</td>
                    <td>Keeps all features, none are removed</td>
                    <td>When many features are correlated and you want stability</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td>Lasso</td>
                    <td>Shrinks coefficients and pushes some to zero</td>
                    <td>Removes less important features</td>
                    <td>When you want a simpler model and feature selection</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td>Elastic Net</td>
                    <td>Combines Ridge and Lasso penalties</td>
                    <td>Shrinks coefficients and can remove some features</td>
                    <td>When features are correlated but you still want feature selection</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td>SVD</td>
                    <td>Reduces data into a smaller number of components</td>
                    <td>Transforms original features into fewer combined components</td>
                    <td>When data has many overlapping or redundant features</td>
                  </tr>
                </tbody>
              </table>
            </div>
            <p style="margin-top:18px;">All methods reduce overfitting, but they do so in different ways—either by controlling coefficients or simplifying the data.</p>
          </div>
          ` : `
          <div class="card">
            <h2 class="subtitle" style="font-size:30px;margin-top:0;">${active.title}</h2>
            <div class="stack" style="gap:20px;margin-top:26px;">
              <div>
                <h3 style="font-size:16px;">What it does</h3>
                <p>${active.what}</p>
              </div>
              <div>
                <h3 style="font-size:16px;">Best when</h3>
                <p>${active.best}</p>
              </div>
              ${active.why ? `
              <div>
                <h3 style="font-size:16px;">Why it helps</h3>
                <p>${active.why}</p>
              </div>
              ` : ""}
              ${active.connection ? `
              <div>
                <h3 style="font-size:16px;">Connection to Regularization</h3>
                <p>${active.connection}</p>
